						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Parakēsarivarmaṉ, Year 9 = c. 10th Century A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>This record an endowment of 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold deposited with the <hi rend="italic">mūlaparaḍai</hi> of Tiruveḷḷaṟai for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruvāṉaikkal Perumānaḍigaḷ by Kumaran Kōn of Iḍaikkāṭṭūr in Kīraṉūr-nāḍu in Pāṇḍi-nāḍu, who was an <hi rend="italic">adigāram</hi> officer under the Chōḻa king.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIX No. 218.]</p>						

